main event: An observer reported seeing circular objects with two distinct lights moving at rapid speeds in Washington, D.C.
interesting points: The circular objects were observed to zig-zag and at times move in a straight line., The observer reported the sighting to the Air Force., The duration of the sighting was brief and lacked physical evidence., The report suggests that the description is consistent with that of an aircraft observed at night., The information was relayed to the Air Force as third-hand account from an individual driving his automobile.
